Refactor operating rules

Use these rules for every task.

Global rules
Preserve existing behavior unless the task explicitly says otherwise.
Do not combine refactoring with feature additions.
Keep diffs narrow and reviewable.
After each task:
run backend tests
run a manual frontend smoke check
Prefer compatibility shims over mass import rewrites.
Do not rename public API routes, websocket event names, or persisted DB fields during these passes.
Definition of done for every task
Project still starts normally.
Existing tests still pass locally.
No known user-facing regression in the smoke checklist.
The old file is smaller and clearer.
The new module has a clear responsibility.
